cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.DS, cs.CG

Reasoning: 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely category as the paper deals with pose estimation algorithms and tracking a quadcopter using kinematic data. 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is also likely as the paper discusses a low-cost IoT wireless system that tracks a quadcopter. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is relevant as the paper mentions the use of coresets in the machine learning community for learning "Big data". 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is relevant as the paper proposes an algorithm for computing a coreset in one pass over an infinite stream of matrices. 
- cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is relevant as the paper deals with the orientation of matrices and the center of mass of a set of matrices.
